examples.en: She was, literally and metaphorically, in perfect shape.
We can think of backlash metaphorically as a bungee cord.
Incense is the resin or sap or, metaphorically, the "blood" of trees.
We thus metaphorically refer to this kind of movement as 'agnostic' movement.
These facts alone allow the term "selection" to be applied metaphorically to the operant case.
